Operation Dudula supporters clashed with police over the arrest of their leader, Nhlanhla 'Lux' Dlamini. He'll be spending the weekend behind bars. eNCA reporter Lindokuhle Xulu has more. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Operation Dudula leader Nhlanhla 'Lux' Dlamini will spend the weekend behind bars. Dlamini was arrested on Thursday after a case of trespassing and theft was opened by the EFF in Dobsonville. READ: Fears that Nhlanhla 'Lux' may be poisoned in jail Despite his appeals for calm, Operation Dudula supporters clashed with police after hearing he would not be released on Friday. * eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports.